					<box></box>
					<textElement textAlignment="Left">
						<font size="12"/>
					</textElement>
				<text><![CDATA[A note to this effect may please be made on the reverse of both halves of P.P.O under your attestation quoting this letter as authority.

A separate bill should be prepared for the payment of the amount quoting this letter as authority.

The dearness allowance relief in pension admissible on the original pension (uncommuted) will continue to be payable with reduced pension. 

The pensioner is informed that if the above amount is found later to be in excess of the which he or she is entitled under the rules he/she will be called upon to refund such excess in one lumpsum.

Please note that payment should be made only on receipt of clear unconditional retirement order issued by the competent authority.

This order is issued subject to recovery of all dues from the retiring person before settlement of retirement benefits and if any dues are found to be recoverable from the retired person at a later date, the person who furnished the ‘no due’ certificate will be held responsible and action will be taken against him and he will be held liable for the unrecovered amount if any.

Before making payment it should be ensured that all the dues to TWAD Board and others i.e. Thrift Society Recover, Bank loan recovery etc., if any are effected from his pensionary benefits.

The receipt of this letter may please be acknowledged along with a certificate to the effect that the entries have been carried out in  both halves of the P.P.O.

]]></text>
				</staticText>
